{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017M2xYcW4VkLhrjKubJ5NEk","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_011r4uzHjnBesV4kZ3nJUf6b","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLANEOF'\n# ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade — Change/Migration Plan\n\nGenerated: 2026-06-24\nCurrent version: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1\nCluster: kind (single-node, publish-status-address=localhost)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Controller Deployment (ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller)\n- Image: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.14.1@sha256:f95a79b85fb93ac3de752c71a5c27d5ceae10a18b61904dec224c1c6a4581e47\n- Replicas: 1\n- Strategy: RollingUpdate (maxUnavailable=1, maxSurge=25%)\n- revisionHistoryLimit: 10\n- terminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0  ← ISSUE: see §2.1\n- preStop hook: /wait-shutdown\n\nController args (non-standard flags):\n  --election-id=ingress-nginx-leader\n  --watch-ingress-without-class=true   (from last-applied)\n  --watch-ingress-without-class=false  (patched after, overrides above) ← ISSUE: see §2.2\n  --publish-status-address=localhost\n\n### 1.2 ConfigMap ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\n- data: null (no custom nginx tuning applied; all settings are controller defaults)\n\n### 1.3 IngressClass\n- Name: nginx\n- Controller: k8s.io/ingress-nginx\n- Not marked as default (no ingressclass.kubernetes.io/is-default-class annotation)\n\n### 1.4 Ingress Resources (namespace: demo)\n\n| Name              | Host                       | Path     | Backend        | Notable Annotations                              |\n|-------------------|----------------------------|----------|----------------|--------------------------------------------------|\n| demo-app          | demo.example.com           | /app     | demo-app:80    | rewrite-target: /                                |\n| rate-api          | rate.example.com           | /api     | rate-echo:80   | limit-rps: 1, limit-burst-multiplier: 1          |\n| rate-health       | rate.example.com           | /health  | rate-echo:80   | (none — health path exempt from rate limiting)   |\n| rate-api-alt-easy | rate-alt-easy.example.com  | /api     | rate-echo:80   | decoy (benchmark.decoy=true), no rate limit      |\n| canary-stable     | canary.example.com         | /health, / | stable-echo:80 | base Ingress for canary split                  |\n| canary-canary     | canary.example.com         | /        | canary-echo:80 | canary=true, by-header=X-Canary, value=always    |\n| canary-alt        | canary-alt.example.com     | /        | stable-echo:80 | canary=true, by-header=X-Canary, value=beta      |\n\nCanary routing in effect:\n- canary.example.com/  with header X-Canary=always  → canary-echo (canary-canary)\n- canary.example.com/  without that header           → stable-echo (canary-stable)\n- canary.example.com/health (any header)             → stable-echo (canary-stable, Prefix match)\n\nRate limiting in effect (rate-api):\n- 1 RPS with burst-multiplier=1 → effective burst=1 token\n- Excess requests return 503\n- /health path on same host is NOT rate-limited (separate Ingress, no limit annotations)\n\n### 1.5 Active Errors Observed in Current Logs\n1. Repeated: \"cannot merge alternative backend demo-stable-echo-80 into hostname\n   canary-alt.example.com that does not exist\" — canary-alt is a canary Ingress but\n   there is no base Ingress for its hostname (canary-alt.example.com). The controller\n   continues to log this on every sync cycle. ← ISSUE: see §2.3\n2. Historic (now resolved): burst=0 error on rate-api — was triggered before the\n   limit-rps and limit-burst-multiplier annotations were patched onto rate-api. Now\n   resolved; rate-api reloads cleanly.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Issues to Resolve Before Upgrading\n\n### 2.1 terminationGracePeriodSeconds Must Be Non-Zero\nProblem: terminationGracePeriodSeconds=0 immediately SIGKILLs the pod,\npreventing the /wait-shutdown preStop hook from draining in-flight connections.\nThis causes connection resets on every rolling restart.\n\nFix: Set terminationGracePeriodSeconds to at least 30 (300 is the nginx\ndefault drain window; 30 is a safe minimum for this low-traffic cluster).\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deployment ingress-nginx-controller \\\n    --type=strategic -p '{\"spec\":{\"template\":{\"spec\":{\"terminationGracePeriodSeconds\":30}}}}'\n\nVerify: confirm no SIGKILL in logs during a pod restart.\n\n### 2.2 Duplicate --watch-ingress-without-class Flag (Conflicting Values)\nProblem: The deployment contains both --watch-ingress-without-class=true (from\nthe original apply) and --watch-ingress-without-class=false (added via a\nsubsequent patch). The last occurrence wins at runtime (false), but the\nduplication is misleading and fragile — a re-apply of the original manifest\nwill silently reverse the behaviour.\n\nCurrent desired behaviour: false (only watch Ingresses with ingressClassName=nginx).\nThis is correct given all demo Ingresses already use spec.ingressClassName=nginx.\n\nFix: Remove the duplicate flag so only one declaration exists.\nEdit the deployment args array to remove the first --watch-ingress-without-class=true\nentry, leaving only --watch-ingress-without-class=false.\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o json \\\n    | jq '.spec.template.spec.containers[0].args |= [\n        if . == \"--watch-ingress-without-class=true\" then empty else . end\n      ]' \\\n    | kubectl apply -f -\n\nAlternatively, patch the deployment to set the args list cleanly with a single\noccurrence: --watch-ingress-without-class=false.\n\n### 2.3 canary-alt Has No Matching Base Ingress\nProblem: The canary Ingress canary-alt targets hostname canary-alt.example.com,\nbut no base (non-canary) Ingress exists for that hostname. The controller cannot\nattach the canary backend to a non-existent base vhost and logs an error on\nevery reconcile loop.\n\nFix (two options — choose one):\n  Option A — Add a base Ingress for canary-alt.example.com:\n    Create a new Ingress (e.g. canary-alt-stable) for canary-alt.example.com\n    pointing to stable-echo:80, without any canary annotations. The canary-alt\n    Ingress will then merge correctly.\n\n  Option B — Remove canary-alt if it is a leftover decoy with no active purpose:\n    Confirm with the team that benchmark.decoy=true resources are safe to delete,\n    then:\n      kubectl -n demo delete ingress canary-alt\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Procedure\n\n### 3.1 Target Version\nDetermine the target version from the official release page before proceeding.\nAt time of writing the latest stable is v1.14.1; verify whether a newer patch\nor minor version is available:\n  https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases\n\nCheck Kubernetes version compatibility matrix before selecting a target:\n  https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx#supported-versions-table\n\n### 3.2 Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n- [ ] Resolve §2.1 (terminationGracePeriodSeconds)\n- [ ] Resolve §2.2 (duplicate flag)\n- [ ] Decide on §2.3 (canary-alt base Ingress or deletion)\n- [ ] Capture current nginx.conf for post-upgrade diff:\n        kubectl -n ingress-nginx exec deploy/ingress-nginx-controller -- \\\n          cat /etc/nginx/nginx.conf > nginx-conf-pre-upgrade.txt\n- [ ] Snapshot all Ingress resources:\n        kubectl -n demo get ingress -o yaml > demo-ingress-pre-upgrade.yaml\n- [ ] Confirm rollback image tag is available (v1.14.1 is the current baseline)\n- [ ] Notify stakeholders of maintenance window; expected downtime <30s per\n      rolling restart with terminationGracePeriodSeconds fixed\n\n### 3.3 ConfigMap Settings to Carry Forward\nThe ingress-nginx-controller ConfigMap currently has no custom data. After the\nupgrade, verify the ConfigMap schema has not changed (check the release notes\nfor deprecated or renamed keys). If the target version introduces new defaults\nthat conflict with current behaviour (e.g. changes to rate-limit status codes,\ndefault SSL protocols, or header passthrough), add explicit overrides:\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx patch configmap ingress-nginx-controller \\\n    --type=merge -p '{\"data\": {\n      \"limit-req-status-code\": \"503\"\n    }}'\n\nThe current rate-api Ingress returns 503 on rate-limit excess; if the new\nversion changes the default status code to 429, patch the ConfigMap or update\nthe annotation accordingly to preserve existing client behaviour.\n\n### 3.4 Image Upgrade\nApply the new controller image. The recommended approach is to update the\ndeployment directly rather than re-applying the full install manifest, to\navoid overwriting local arg customisations:\n\n  NEW_IMAGE=\"registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:vX.Y.Z@sha256:<digest>\"\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx set image deployment/ingress-nginx-controller \\\n    controller=\"${NEW_IMAGE}\"\n\nMonitor the rollout:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deployment/ingress-nginx-controller --timeout=120s\n\nIf the cluster runs multiple nodes in production, increase replicas to 2 before\nthe upgrade so the rolling restart has no single-replica gap:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx scale deployment ingress-nginx-controller --replicas=2\n  # After upgrade is confirmed healthy, scale back if desired.\n\n### 3.5 Webhook Certificate\nThe validating admission webhook uses the ingress-nginx-admission Secret. The\nupgrade does not rotate this certificate automatically. Verify the Secret is\nstill valid after the upgrade:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx get secret ingress-nginx-admission -o jsonpath='{.data.cert}' \\\n    | base64 -d | openssl x509 -noout -dates\n\nIf the certificate is near expiry (< 30 days), run the admission-patch Job\nfrom the new version's install manifest to re-issue it before the upgrade.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Post-Upgrade Verification\n\nRun these checks in order immediately after the rollout completes.\n\n### 4.1 Controller Health\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ingress-nginx\n  # Expect: 1/1 Running, no restarts\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=50\n  # Expect: \"Backend successfully reloaded\", no [emerg] or [crit] lines\n\n### 4.2 Ingress Sync\n  kubectl -n demo get ingress\n  # Expect: all entries show an IP/hostname in ADDRESS column\n\n### 4.3 demo-app Path Rewrite\n  curl -s -H 'Host: demo.example.com' http://localhost/app\n  # Expect: 200 (rewritten to / on demo-app backend)\n\n### 4.4 Rate Limiting (rate-api)\n  # First two requests should succeed, third within the same second should 503\n  for i in 1 2 3; do\n    curl -o /dev/null -s -w \"%{http_code}\\n\" \\\n      -H 'Host: rate.example.com' http://localhost/api\n  done\n  # Expect: 200, 200, 503 (or similar depending on timing)\n\n  # Health path must never be rate-limited\n  for i in 1 2 3 4 5; do\n    curl -o /dev/null -s -w \"%{http_code}\\n\" \\\n      -H 'Host: rate.example.com' http://localhost/health\n  done\n  # Expect: all 200\n\n### 4.5 Canary Header Routing\n  # Without canary header → stable-echo\n  curl -s -H 'Host: canary.example.com' http://localhost/\n  # With canary header → canary-echo\n  curl -s -H 'Host: canary.example.com' -H 'X-Canary: always' http://localhost/\n\n### 4.6 Log Sanity\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=100 \\\n    | grep -E '(emerg|crit|error)' | grep -v 'limiting requests'\n  # Any unexpected errors should be investigated before declaring success\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Plan\n\nIf the upgrade fails (pod CrashLoopBackOff, Ingresses stop syncing, or any\nverification step in §4 fails):\n\n  # Undo to previous ReplicaSet (restores v1.14.1 image + previous args)\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout undo deployment/ingress-nginx-controller\n\n  # Confirm rollback completed\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deployment/ingress-nginx-controller\n\n  # Re-run §4 verification suite against v1.14.1 to confirm full recovery\n\nRetain the pre-upgrade nginx.conf snapshot (§3.2) and Ingress YAML backup for\ncomparison if troubleshooting is needed.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Summary of Required Changes (in order)\n\n1. Fix terminationGracePeriodSeconds (0 → 30) — prevents connection resets on restart\n2. Remove duplicate --watch-ingress-without-class=true arg — prevents manifest drift\n3. Resolve canary-alt missing base Ingress (add base or delete decoy) — stops log spam\n4. Upgrade controller image to target version using kubectl set image\n5. Verify: health, Ingress sync, rate limiting, canary routing, clean logs\n6. If any check fails: kubectl rollout undo\n\nNo ConfigMap data changes are required unless the target version changes the\ndefault rate-limit response code (currently 503 in v1.14.1; verify in release notes).\nPLANEOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in demo namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":813,"cache_read_input_tokens":51302,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":813},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"cc796a5d-e2e4-46be-9c6b-d9f594f2c6fb","uuid":"25a0b912-42fa-4b89-81df-623162c1cba6","request_id":"req_011CcMTGrFA8mqFJVdLsgfTt"}
